<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:s="https://admin.wvusports.com/services/xml_schema/story" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/"><channel><title>West Virginia University Athletics</title><link>https://admin.wvusports.com/rss.aspx</link><description>Latest news items for West Virginia University Athletics</description><atom:link href="https://admin.wvusports.com/rss" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml" /><language>en-us</language><ttl>60</ttl><item><title>WVU to Play Pitt at PPG Paints Arena</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/18/mens-basketball-wvu-to-play-pitt-at-ppg-paints-arena</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/18/mens-basketball-wvu-to-play-pitt-at-ppg-paints-arena</guid><category>Men's Basketball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="West Virginia and Pitt will meet on Dec. 9 at PPG Paints Arena " src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/18/MBB26-27_BackyardBBClassic_1920x1080_NoBYB.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The 193rd edition of the men's basketball Backyard Brawl will take place at PPG Paints Arena in downtown Pittsburgh on Wednesday, Dec. 9.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/18/MBB26-27_BackyardBBClassic_1920x1080_NoBYB.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/18/MBB26-27_BackyardBBClassic_1920x1080_NoBYB.jpg"><media:title>West Virginia and Pitt will meet on Dec. 9 at PPG Paints Arena </media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/18/MBB26-27_BackyardBBClassic_1920x1080_NoBYB.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Thu, 18 Jun 2026 15:00:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>4</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59202</s:story_id></item><item><title>West Virginia's Season Comes to an End at College World Series</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/17/west-virginias-season-comes-to-an-end-at-college-world-series</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/17/west-virginias-season-comes-to-an-end-at-college-world-series</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Baseball Team Huddle postgame after a game against North Carolina at the College World Series" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/17/WVU_BSB_G4_CWS_v_UNC-153.jpg" /><br /><br />OMAHA, Neb. – The No. 16 West Virginia University baseball team saw its season come to a close on Wednesday with a 12-6 loss to No. 5 North Carolina. The Mountaineers end their best season in program history with a 47-17 overall record as one the final four teams remaining in the country.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/17/WVU_BSB_G4_CWS_v_UNC-153.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/17/WVU_BSB_G4_CWS_v_UNC-153.jpg"><media:title>Baseball Team Huddle postgame after a game against North Carolina at the College World Series</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/17/WVU_BSB_G4_CWS_v_UNC-153.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Wed, 17 Jun 2026 19:45:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59201</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Shut Out Troy to Stay Alive in College World Series</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/16/baseball-mountaineers-shut-out-troy-to-stay-alive-in-college-world-series</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/16/baseball-mountaineers-shut-out-troy-to-stay-alive-in-college-world-series</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Dawson Montesa throws a pitch against Troy in the College World Series" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/16/EEN01627.jpg" /><br /><br />OMAHA, Neb. – The No. 16 West Virginia University baseball team staved off elimination with a 12-0 victory over Troy, Tuesday afternoon at Charles Schwab Field. The Mountaineers improve to 47-16 while the Trojans finish their season at 39-32.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/16/EEN01627.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/16/EEN01627.jpg"><media:title>Dawson Montesa throws a pitch against Troy in the College World Series</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/16/EEN01627.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Tue, 16 Jun 2026 21:12:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59199</s:story_id></item><item><title>'I was happy for the program as much as I was for me': 1987 All-American Talks Career, Current Trajectory of WVU Wrestling</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/17/-i-was-happy-for-the-program-as-much-as-i-was-for-me-1987-all-american-talks-career-current-trajectory-of-wvu-wrestling</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/17/-i-was-happy-for-the-program-as-much-as-i-was-for-me-1987-all-american-talks-career-current-trajectory-of-wvu-wrestling</guid><category>Wrestling</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Jim Akerly wrestled for the WVU wrestling program in the 1980s, becoming an All-American in 1987." src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/17/jim-akerly_2.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. — It's one thing to wrestle at the collegiate level for four seasons. It's another thing to wrestle for that long at West Virginia University after initially joining the program as a walk-on.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/17/jim-akerly_2.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/17/jim-akerly_2.jpg"><media:title>Jim Akerly wrestled for the WVU wrestling program in the 1980s, becoming an All-American in 1987.</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/17/jim-akerly_2.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Wed, 17 Jun 2026 09:44:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>18</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59200</s:story_id></item><item><title>CSC Academic All-District Men and Women’s At-Large Team Released</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/16/general-csc-academic-all-district-men-and-womens-at-large-team-released</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/16/general-csc-academic-all-district-men-and-womens-at-large-team-released</guid><category>General, Rifle, Wrestling</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Woodburn Hall" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2018/3/28/Campus.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. -- The College Sports Communicators (CSC) announced the 2026 Academic All-District At-Large Teams for both men's and women's sports on Tuesday, which featured 10 Mountaineer student-athletes.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2018/3/28/Campus.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2018/3/28/Campus.jpg"><media:title>Woodburn Hall</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2018/3/28/Campus.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Tue, 16 Jun 2026 12:00:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>3</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59196</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers to Face Troy in Elimination Game</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/15/baseball-mountaineers-to-face-troy-in-elimination-game</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/15/baseball-mountaineers-to-face-troy-in-elimination-game</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Armani Guzman" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/15/WVU_BSB_G2_CWS_v_UNC-47.jpeg" /><br /><br />OMAHA, Neb. – The West Virginia University baseball team continues its stay in the College World Series with an elimination game against Troy on Tuesday, June 16, at Charles Schwab Field. First pitch is scheduled for 2 p.m. ET.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/15/WVU_BSB_G2_CWS_v_UNC-47.jpeg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/15/WVU_BSB_G2_CWS_v_UNC-47.jpeg"><media:title>Armani Guzman</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/15/WVU_BSB_G2_CWS_v_UNC-47.jpeg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Mon, 15 Jun 2026 17:18:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59195</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Fall to No. 5 North Carolina in College World Series</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/14/baseball-mountaineers-fall-to-no-5-north-carolina-in-college-world-series</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/14/baseball-mountaineers-fall-to-no-5-north-carolina-in-college-world-series</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Sean Smith runs the bases against North Carolina" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/14/EEN06717.jpg" /><br /><br />OMAHA, Neb. – The No. 16 West Virginia University baseball team fell to No. 5 North Carolina, 5-2, Sunday evening in the Men's College World Series at Charles Schwab Field. The Mountaineers drop to 46-16 while the Tar Heels improve to 52-12-1.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/14/EEN06717.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/14/EEN06717.jpg"><media:title>Sean Smith runs the bases against North Carolina</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/14/EEN06717.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sun, 14 Jun 2026 23:29:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59194</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Close NCAA Championships with Three All-Americans</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/14/track-field-mountaineers-close-ncaa-championships-with-three-all-americans</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/14/track-field-mountaineers-close-ncaa-championships-with-three-all-americans</guid><category>Track &amp; Field</category><descri